sorcer.core.requestor
Class ServiceRequestor

java.lang.Object
  sorcer.core.requestor.ServiceRequestor
All Implemented Interfaces:
Requestor, SorcerConstants
public abstract class ServiceRequestor
extends Object
implements Requestor, SorcerConstants

The abstract class with the methods that define the initialization and behavior of a service requestor. This class uses SorcerConstants and requires subclasses to implement sorcer.core.requestor.Requestor#getExertion method. The main method of the class initializes requestor properties and calls methods of the {@link sorcer.core.requestor.Requestor} interface accordingly. It attempts to create a new instance of the requestor defined by a subclass extending {@link sorcer.core.requestor.ServiceRequestor}. If an internal class server (webster) is needed then it attempts to start it with given class root paths that define the codebase of the underlying service requestor.

Author:
M. W. Sobolewski
See Also:

loadProperties

public void loadProperties(String filename)
Loads service requestor properties from a filename file. By default a service requestor loads its properties from requestor.properties file located in the requestor's package. Also, a service requestor properties file name can be specified as a system property when starting the requestor with -DrequestorProperties=<filename>. In this case the requestor loads properties from filename file. Properties are accessible calling the getProperty(String) method.

Parameters:
filename - the properties file name see #getProperty
